  OS: Windows 10 10.0.22000
  CPU: (12) x64 AMD Ryzen 5 2600 Six-Core Processor
Binaries:
  Node: 18.8.0 - ~\AppData\Local\Temp\xfs-922b0091\node.CMD
  Yarn: 4.0.0-rc.31 - ~\AppData\Local\Temp\xfs-922b0091\yarn.CMD
  npm: 8.18.0 - C:\Program Files\nodejs\npm.CMD
```


### Additional context

The code in Yarn at fault (?) is the following:
https://github.com/yarnpkg/berry/blob/84c62e649c91883f37dc8faff13fdb24cd5e7ba2/packages/yarnpkg-nm/sources/buildNodeModulesTree.ts
from commit 45d3437f259ad6f6ddf0a60a96dc18c9aa73b091 just preluding the release of https://github.com/yarnpkg/berry/releases/tag/%40yarnpkg%2Fcli%2F3.3.0

It's the `!isCircularSymlink` which I'm sure has a good use-case, hence why I'm not sure this is a bug or not - or if there's any way to get around it.
 
Check that the above reproduction works with yarn v3.2.4: [Playground](https://yarnpkg.com/playground?%3D%3D)

