### Describe the bug

When trying to install a package tarball that references another package tarball via a relative path, yarn fails to resolve the referenced tarball. To reproduce, create the following file structure:
* `package.json`, references `file:./package-2.tgz`
* `package-2.tgz`, contains `package/package.json` which references `file:./package-1.tgz`
* `package-1.tgz`, contains `package/package.json`

It looks like yarn tries resolving from the installed location (node_modules) instead of the source tarball location. The same works fine when using `npm`, or when using absolute paths (`file:/path/to/package-1.tgz`) with yarn.

